                            <comment id="12627800" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Tue, 2 Sep 2008 21:28:02 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;First pass at updating solrconfig.xml, removing deprecated request handlers and tweaking some other config items.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12627856" author="hossman" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2008 00:53:12 +0100"  >
&lt;p&gt;Question: you&apos;ve replaced DisMaxRequestHandler with StandardRequestHandler and uses of defType ... but StandardRequestHandler is just an empty subclass of SearchHandler ... is there any reason not to just use SearchHandler directly?  (for that matter: does anyone remember why we didn&apos;t deprecate StandardRequestHandler?  .. I actually thought we had.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Comment: we should probably move the &quot;spellcheck&quot; &amp;lt;component&amp;gt; declaration (and thus the &quot;/spellCheckCompRH&quot; &amp;lt;requestHandler&amp;gt;) to after the explanation of what components are.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12627880" author="hossman" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2008 02:05:18 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Do people think QParsers and ValueSourceParsers warrant mention in the example configs? (perhaps commented out like the list of default ResponseWriters)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12628034" author="otis" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2008 17:12:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hoss, I think so, yes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
